President Kenyatta also rubbished claims that the BBI is aimed at creating additional seats for a select few.  President Uhuru Kenyatta yesterday took the BBI charm offensive to the youth — a group critical in passing the document due to its large numbers — and asked them to support the plan to amend the Constitution “for a better future and country”.
The Head of State, who was speaking to a group of youths at the Bomas of Kenya, said the BBI document had placed them at its centre. He added that the report is key in addressing some of the problems that have bedevilled the country, including high unemployment rate among young people.



