The President, who spoke during the unveiling of the KenyaNiMimi youth campaign, said the 2018 handshake with ODM leader Raila Odinga was a testament of what the country could achieve should it adopt the proposed constitutional changes, by embracing the politics of ideologies, versus that of hate and negative ethnicity.
“From that handshake , you have seen the peace that has prevailed in this country and the manner in which we have been able to work together because our agendas and not that different.”
The KenyaNiMimi campaign, launched by Youth Affairs ministry in partnership with the United Nations Population Fund, aims to bring young people together to promote their health and well-being. The talks aim to reach consensus before referendum signatures are handed to IEBC. Revised BBI Bill full of goodies to lawmakers who will be crucial to the success of the referendum. The Treasury CS last week announced that temporary Covid-19 tax reliefs will expire at the end of the year. Speaker gives IEBC leeway to prepare for and conduct a by-election following the death of MP Justus Murunga. Protesting learners said the student was attacked on Saturday morning while taking a bath just before the morning preps.